Chronic sleep deprivation can stress the heart, increasing the risk of cardiovascular disease and death.
Studies show that insufficient sleep disrupts circadian rhythms, impacting cardiac function.
Research reveals a link between wake-up times and cardiovascular health, with early risers at higher risk.
Athletes and students often face sleep deprivation, affecting performance and health.
Napping has benefits, aiding memory and reducing weight gain.
Lack of sleep can lead to obesity, diabetes, and cardiovascular issues.
Addressing sleep problems in adolescents may prevent substance use.
Sleep plays a crucial role in overall health and well-being, impacting physical and mental functions.
